025%2C%20individuals%20can%20contribute%20%244%2C300%20to%20an%20HSA)%2C%20not%20touching%20the%20money%2C%20and%20letting%20it%20grow%20tax-free.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20major%20perk%20of%20the%20account%20is%20its%20three-pronged%20tax%20benefit%3A%20You%20can%20contribute%20pretax%20dollars%20(reducing%20your%20taxable%20income)%2C%20your%20contributions%20and%20earnings%20grow%20tax-free%20over%20time%2C%20and%20you%20can%20withdraw%20your%20money%20tax-free%20to%20cover%20qualified%20medical%20expenses.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20self-made%20millionaire%20I%20spoke%20to%2C%20who%20has%20his%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-millionaire-uses-health-savings-account-has-to-build-wealth-2023-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Einvestments%20spread%20across%20seven%20types%20of%20accounts%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20told%20me%20that%20his%20HSA%20is%20his%20%26quot%3Bfavorite%20by%20far.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20a%20great%20account%2C%20and%20one%20that%20I%20have%20access%20to%20since%20I'm%20enrolled%20in%20a%20high-deductible%20health%20plan%20(HDHP).%20Note%20that%20an%20HDHP%2C%20which%20offers%20a%20lower%20premium%20but%20comes%20with%20a%20higher%20deductible%2C%20is%20not%20the%20best%20choice%20for%20everyone.%20It's%20typically%20well%20suited%20for%20people%20who%20are%20very%20healthy%2C%20don't%20plan%20on%20seeking%20medical%20care%20frequently%2C%20and%20can%20afford%20to%20pay%20the%20deductible%20upfront%20in%20the%20event%20of%20a%20medical%20event.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20two%20years%20of%20simply%20saving%20in%20an%20HSA%20while%20writing%20about%20millionaires%20who%20are%20putting%20that%20money%20to%20work%2C%20I%20decided%20to%20do%20the%20same%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwealth-building-strategy-rich-use-invest-hsa-max-out-plan-2024-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Einvested%20about%20%244%2C400%20worth%20of%20my%20HSA%20dollars%3C%2Fa%3E%20into%20a%20target%20date%20fund%20in%20early%202024.%20I%20calculated%20that%20if%20I%20continued%20to%20max%20out%20my%20account%20and%20invest%20my%20HSA%20dollars%20for%20the%20next%2030%20years%2C%20it%20could%20mean%20about%20a%20%24200%2C000%20difference%20in%20net%20worth.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20used%20strategically%2C%20an%20HSA%20can%20be%20a%20powerful%20tool.%20However%2C%20like%20many%20financial%20products%20and%20services%2C%20there's%20fine%20print%20that's%20important%20to%20be%20aware%20of%20and%20easy%20to%20overlook%2C%20especially%20when%20you're%20thinking%20about%20the%20six-figure%20dollar%20amount%20you%20just%20tacked%20onto%20your%20nest%20egg.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22139cd60f-1936-445a-9a59-e8320527192f%5C%22%3ECheck%20the%20fees%20associated%20with%20your%20account%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EPrior%20to%20the%20HSA%20transfer%2C%20which%20I%20initiated%20to%20consolidate%20two%20different%20accounts%2C%20I%20hadn't%20bothered%20looking%20under%20the%20hood%20of%20either%20account.%20However%2C%20before%20transferring%20one%20to%20the%20next%2C%20certified%20financial%20planner%20Brent%20Weiss%20recommended%20I%20compare%20the%20two.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20told%20me%20they%20could%20be%20notably%20different%3A%20%26quot%3BWhen%20it%20comes%20to%20an%20HSA%2C%20there%20is%20a%20big%20disparity%20in%20the%20quality%20of%20HSA%20providers%20within%20the%20industry.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20I%20asked%20what%20makes%20a%20%26quot%3Bgood%26quot%3B%20HSA%20provider%2C%20he%20pointed%20to%20two%20main%20factors%3A%20fees%20and%20investment%20options.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat's%20when%20I%20found%20the%20investment%20account%20fees%20associated%20with%20both%20accounts%3A%20One%20was%200.40%25%20annually%2C%20billed%20monthly%20and%20capped%20at%20%2410%20a%20month%20regardless%20of%20the%20account%20balance.%20The%20other%20was%200.60%25%2C%20invoiced%20quarterly%20at%200.15%25.%20I%20would%20later%20find%20out%20that%20the%200.60%25%20fee%20wasn't%20even%20charged%20by%20the%20HSA%20provider%20but%2C%20rather%2C%20by%20the%20provider's%20investment%20partner.%20It%20was%20a%20good%20reminder%20that%20sometimes%20fees%20can%20be%20difficult%20to%20find%20and%20understand.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20first%20glance%2C%20the%20fees%20seemed%20low%2C%20but%20Weiss%20seemed%20to%20think%20otherwise.%20He%20asked%20if%20I%20meant%20to%20say%200.04%25%20and%200.06%25%2C%20rather%20than%200.40%25%20and%200.60%25.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETo%20attach%20a%20dollar%20amount%20to%20the%20fee%2C%20we%20referred%20to%20my%20recent%20transactions%20and%20found%20that%20I%20was%20billed%20about%20%247%20quarterly.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221664%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22hsa%20transfer%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F68374582ca50259add4d3583%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22594%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E%3Cp%3EKathleen%20Elkins%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThat's%20a%20less%20shocking%20figure%20than%20the%20percentage%2C%20he%20said%3A%20%26quot%3BIt's%20not%20a%20huge%20dollar%20amount%20today%20because%20of%20the%20size%20of%20the%20balance.%26quot%3B%20However%2C%20he%20added%20that%20%26quot%3Bfees%20matter%20and%20they%20do%20add%20up%20over%20time.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22f32e3044-1a18-4669-a840-7148d011733c%5C%22%3EHow%20much%20do%20fees%20add%20up%3F%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20I'm%20fine%20paying%20about%20%247%20a%20quarter%20or%20%2428%20a%20year%20in%20fees%20for%20now%2C%20as%20Weiss%20mentioned%2C%20that%20number%20could%20look%20much%20different%20the%20more%20my%20accounts%20grow.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETo%20find%20out%20exactly%20how%20much%2C%20I%20turned%20to%20ChatGPT%20to%20run%20the%20numbers%20for%20both%20fee%20structures.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20laid%20out%20the%20scenario%20as%20follows%2C%20including%20details%20such%20as%20the%20%2410%20monthly%20cap.%20I%20also%20mentioned%20that%20I%20planned%20to%20max%20the%20account%20out%20each%20year%20for%20the%20next%2030%20years%2C%20and%20reminded%20it%20that%20the%20contribution%20limit%20tends%20to%20increase%20over%20time%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cblockquote%3E%3Csection%3EHello!%20I'm%20trying%20to%20figure%20out%20how%20much%20I%20would%20owe%20in%20fees%20by%20continuing%20to%20invest%20in%20my%20HSAs.%20There%20are%20two%20different%20fee%20structures.%20For%20the%20first%2C%20the%20annual%20investment%20account%20fee%20is%200.4%25%2C%20billed%20monthly%20and%20capped%20at%20%2410%20a%20month.%20For%20the%20second%2C%20the%20annual%20investment%20account%20fee%20is%200.60%25%2C%20invoiced%20quarterly%20at%200.15%25.%20There%20does%20not%20appear%20to%20be%20a%20monthly%20cap%20on%20the%20second.%20Currently%2C%20I%20have%20%244%2C800%20invested%20and%20I%20plan%20to%20contribute%20and%20invest%20the%20maximum%20each%20year%2C%20which%20is%20%244%2C300%20for%20individuals.%20Assuming%20I%20invest%20the%20maximum%2C%20which%20tends%20to%20increase%20each%20year%20(in%202026%2C%20it's%20%244%2C400)%2C%20for%20the%20next%2030%20years%20until%20retirement%2C%20how%20much%20would%20I%20be%20paying%20in%20fees%20for%20both%20accounts%3F%3C%2Fsection%3E%3C%2Fblockquote%3E%3Cp%3EA%20few%20seconds%20later%2C%20the%20results%20were%20in.%20Here's%20what%20ChatGPT%20told%20me%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cblockquote%3E%3Csection%3EOver%20the%20next%2030%20years%2C%20assuming%20steady%20contributions%20and%20a%207%25%20annual%20return%3A%3C%2Fsection%3E%3Csection%3EFee%20Structure%201%20(0.4%25%20annually%2C%20capped%20at%20%2410%2Fmonth)%3A%20You%20would%20pay%20approximately%20%3Cstrong%3E%243%2C363%20in%20total%20fees%3C%2Fstrong%3E.%3C%2Fsection%3E%3Csection%3EFee%20Structure%202%20(0.6%25%20annually%2C%20billed%20quarterly%20at%200.15%25%2C%20uncapped)%3A%20You%20would%20pay%20approximately%20%3Cstrong%3E%2430%2C054%20in%20total%20fees%3C%2Fstrong%3E.%3C%2Fsection%3E%3Csection%3EThe%20capped%20structure%20saves%20you%20significantly%20over%20time%20%E2%80%94%20by%20about%20%3Cstrong%3E%2426%2C691%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20%E2%80%94%20thanks%20to%20the%20monthly%20cap%20limiting%20fees%20as%20your%20investments%20grow.%3C%2Fsection%3E%3C%2Fblockquote%3E%3Cp%3EAn%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.schwabmoneywise.com%2Finvestment-fees-calculator%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eonline%20fee%20calculator%3C%2Fa%3E%20confirmed%20that%20fees%20can%20indeed%20add%20up%20significantly%20over%20time%2C%20though%20I%20didn't%20have%20the%20option%20to%20include%20the%20%2410%20cap%20and%20change%20my%20annual%20contribution%20amount%20to%20reflect%20future%20contribution%20limit%20increases.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20I%20haven't%20made%20any%20adjustments%20to%20my%20HSA%20investment%20strategy%20yet%2C%20I%20now%20have%20more%20information.%20I%20also%20learned%20to%20look%20out%20for%20monthly%20maintenance%20fees%20associated%20with%20accounts%20like%20HSAs%2C%20transfer%20fees%20or%20fees%20associated%20with%20closing%20an%20account%2C%20and%20expense%20ratios%20(fees%20that%20mutual%20funds%20and%20ETFs%20charge%20investors).%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20the%20fees%20ever%20become%20too%20much%20to%20stomach%2C%20I%20can%20always%20consider%20a%20strategy%20Weiss%20mentioned%20and%20uses%20himself%3A%20Contributing%20to%20a%20different%20HSA%20provider%20than%20the%20one%20offered%20by%20your%20company.%20I%20incorrectly%20assumed%20you%20were%20stuck%20with%20whichever%20provider%20your%20company%20elected.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BYou%20can%20go%20anywhere%20you%20want%2C%20set%20up%20your%20own%20HSA%20account%2C%20make%20your%20own%20contributions%20to%20it%2C%20and%20deduct%20it%20on%20your%20tax%20returns%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BI%20just%20do%20an%20electronic%20transfer%20once%20a%20year%20to%20make%20my%20annual%20contribution.%20I%20make%20sure%20it's%20listed%20on%20my%20tax%20return%20because%20it%20doesn't%20flow%20through%20my%20W-2%2C%20so%20I%20have%20to%20deduct%20it%20on%20my%20tax%20returns.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20more%20complicated%20than%20simply%20electing%20a%20percentage%20of%20your%20paycheck%20to%20have%20your%20employer%20send%20straight%20to%20your%20HSA%2C%20and%20he%20mentioned%20one%20catch%20to%20keep%20in%20mind%3A%20%26quot%3BThe%20only%20downside%20is%20that%20if%20your%20income%20is%20under%20the%20Social%20Security%20wage%20base%2C%20you%20actually%20don't%20pay%20FICA%20tax%20on%20direct%20HSA%20contributions%2C%20so%20there%20can%20be%20a%20tax-savings%20on%20that%20contribution.%20But%2C%20if%20your%20income%20is%20over%20the%20Social%20Security%20wage%20base%2C%20then%20you're%20not%20really%20saving%20a%20ton%20of%20money%20by%20doing%20it%20on%20your%20own.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20now%2C%20I'm%20content%20sticking%20with%20the%20less%20complex%20model%20of%20contributing%20to%20the%20plan%20provided%20by%20my%20company.%20But%20I%20learned%20to%20always%20read%20the%20fine%20print%20and%20to%20not%20only%20find%20the%20fees%20%E2%80%94%20but%20to%20run%20the%20numbers%20to%20understand%20exactly%20how%20they%20could%20impact%20your%20portfolio.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-much-annual-investment-account-fees-can-affect-net-worth-2025-6%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1749115801000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F68408f9d9b2a601d01b24e7a%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-much-annual-investment-account-fees-can-affect-net-worth-2025-6%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22ChatGPT%20helped%20me%20figure%20out%20exactly%20how%20much%20I%20could%20owe%20in%20investment%20account%20fees%20over%20time%20%E2%80%94%20and%20it%20was%20a%20five-figure%20number.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22kelkins%40businessinsider.com%20(Kathleen%20Elkins)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A14%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-much-annual-investment-account-fees-can-affect-