-musk-trump-big-beautiful-bill-disgusting-abomination-2025-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3E%26quot%3Ba%20disgusting%20abomination%26quot%3B%20%3C%2Fa%3Eon%20X%2C%20won't%20make%20sense%20for%20most%20people.%20But%20career%20experts%20said%20there%20are%20other%2C%20more%20practical%20ways%20to%20deliver%20negative%20feedback%20to%20a%20superior.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BNo%20one%20recommends%20taking%20to%20social%20media%20to%20criticize%20your%20boss%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20organizational%20psychologist%20Alison%20Fragale%2C%20especially%20if%20your%20name%20is%20attached%20and%20you're%20seriously%20looking%20to%20drive%20change.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThough%20you%20might%20get%20a%20lot%20of%20thumbs%20up%2C%20it%20also%20comes%20with%20a%20lot%20of%20risky%20downside%2C%26quot%3B%20Fragale%20told%20Business%20Insider.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22fdf1fd10-568f-4c77-add9-5066393bbb51%5C%22%3EGetting%20loud%20generally%20isn't%20the%20best%20strategy%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20one%20of%20the%20world's%20richest%20men%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Felon-musk%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EMusk%20%3C%2Fa%3Eis%20uniquely%20insulated%20when%20airing%20grievances.%20The%20CEO%20of%20Tesla%2C%20Space%20X%2C%20and%20several%20other%20companies%20wields%20exceptional%20power%20and%20status%2C%20and%20being%20outspoken%20is%20part%20of%20his%20personal%20brand.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20the%20rest%20of%20us%2C%20taking%20an%20offline%2C%20confidential%20approach%20to%20voicing%20discontent%20is%20generally%20best%20since%20it%20avoids%20embarrassing%20the%20recipient%20and%20inviting%20backlash%2C%20said%20Yale%20University%20management%20professor%20Jeffrey%20Sonnenfeld.%20That's%20a%20lesson%20many%20big-company%20CEOs%20have%20used%20in%20recent%20weeks%20to%20push%20back%20against%20the%20president's%20significant%20tariff%20hikes.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThey've%20managed%20through%20private%20collective%20action%20to%20get%20him%20to%20move%20considerably%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Sonnenfeld.%20%26quot%3BThey%20went%20in%20with%20the%20facts.%20They%20didn't%20try%20to%20publicly%20humiliate%20him.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdonald-trump-elon-musk-budget-bill-response-attack-explained-why-2025-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EMusk%20didn't%20call%20out%20Trump%3C%2Fa%3E%20by%20name%20in%20his%20social-media%20posts%20criticizing%20the%20president's%20bill%2C%20which%20includes%20cuts%20to%20Medicaid%20and%20an%20extension%20of%20the%20tax%20cuts%20that%20Trump%20and%20Republicans%20enacted%20in%202017.%20His%20messages%2C%20though%2C%20land%20as%20a%20personal%20attack%20because%20Trump%20has%20been%20aggressively%20touting%20the%20bill%2C%20calling%20it%20%26quot%3Bbeautiful%26quot%3B%20and%20pushing%20for%20Congress%20to%20pass%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20will%20be%20the%20biggest%20Tax%20Cut%20for%20Middle%20and%20Working%20Class%20Americans%20by%20far%2C%26quot%3B%20Trump%20wrote%20on%20Truth%20Social%20last%20month.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftrump-big-beautiful-bill-impact-tesla-xai-elon-musk-2025-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EMusk%20has%20said%20that%20the%20bill%3C%2Fa%3E%20will%20increase%20the%20nation's%20already%20bloated%20deficit%2C%20undermining%20the%20months%20of%20work%20he%20put%20in%20at%20the%20Trump%20administration's%20Department%20of%20Government%20Efficiency.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOn%20Wednesday%2C%20Musk%20asked%20Americans%20to%20take%20action%20to%20try%20to%20stop%20the%20bill%20from%20passing.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BCall%20your%20Senator%2C%20Call%20your%20Congressman%2C%20bankrupting%20America%20is%20NOT%20ok!%20KILL%20the%20BILL%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said%20on%20X.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22cfe9b2d7-f7d7-42f8-a3fd-3ce42181131c%5C%22%3EWhen%20and%20how%20to%20raise%20concerns%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20workplace%2C%20career%20gurus%20generally%20advise%20people%20to%20only%20pipe%20up%20about%20concerns%20that%20impact%20multiple%20workers%20or%20a%20company%20at%20large.%20Personal%20grievances%20are%20best%20handled%20through%20a%20direct%20manager%2C%20human%20resources%2C%20or%20an%20employer's%20complaint%20hotline.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BNot%20every%20truth%20needs%20to%20be%20said%20out%20loud%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Fragale.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20collective%20voice%20creates%20legitimacy%2C%20which%20is%20why%20she%20also%20recommends%20gathering%20allies%20and%20having%20at%20least%20one%20by%20your%20side%20when%20you're%20ready%20to%20speak%20out.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EConsider%20whether%20you're%20the%20best%20person%20to%20raise%20the%20matter%20to%20someone%20at%20the%20top%20of%20the%20corporate%20ladder%20if%20you%20lack%20status%20or%20haven't%20earned%20the%20person's%20respect.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20have%20outsourced%20almost%20every%20aspect%20of%20my%20kids'%20education%2C%20not%20because%20I%20don't%20know%20how%20to%20swim%20or%20ride%20a%20bike%2C%20but%20because%20they%20won't%20listen%20to%20me%2C%26quot%3B%20Fragale%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMeanwhile%2C%20keep%20in%20mind%20that%20you%20may%20not%20have%20all%20the%20facts%20as%20to%20why%20a%20superior%20made%20whatever%20decision%20you%20have%20beef%20with%2C%20said%20Bill%20George%2C%20an%20executive%20fellow%20at%20Harvard%20Business%20School.%20It's%20possible%20your%20criticism%20is%20unwarranted%2C%20so%20he%20recommends%20couching%20your%20critique%20as%20being%20based%20on%20what%20you%20know.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BSometimes%20CEOs%20have%20to%20make%20decisions%20for%20reasons%20that%20aren't%20apparent%2C%26quot%3B%20George%2C%20who%20was%20CEO%20of%20the%20health-technology%20company%20Medtronic%20earlier%20in%20his%20career%2C%20said.%20%26quot%3BYou%20have%20to%20understand%20the%20whole%20context.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOnly%20speak%20up%20to%20a%20superior%20when%20you%20have%20something%20meaningful%20to%20point%20out%2C%20said%20Candice%20Pokk%2C%20a%20senior%20consultant%20at%20human-resources%20consulting%20firm%20Segal.%20%26quot%3BIt%20needs%20to%20rise%20to%20the%20level%20of%20their%20position%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESome%20business%20leaders%20say%20they%20are%20receptive%20to%20negative%20feedback%20as%20long%20as%20it's%20conveyed%20respectfully.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20George%20was%20Medtronic's%20CEO%2C%20a%20manager%20privately%20told%20him%20that%20he'd%20hurt%20several%20employees'%20feelings%20during%20a%20group%20meeting.%20Though%20he%20stood%20by%20the%20substance%20of%20his%20remarks%2C%20he%20apologized%20for%20how%20he%20relayed%20them%20and%20said%20the%20feedback%20made%20him%20think%20differently%20about%20his%20communication%20style.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20caused%20me%20to%20reflect%20on%20it%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETo%20share%20negative%20feedback%2C%20start%20with%20something%20positive%20and%20authentic%20about%20the%20individual%20before%20launching%20into%20critisicm%2C%20and%20keep%20it%20brief%2C%20Pokk%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BExecutives%20want%20information%20that's%20bite-sized%20and%20easy%20to%20understand%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDishing%20criticism%20to%20someone%20in%20a%20more%20powerful%20position%20can%20be%20nerve-racking%2C%20no%20matter%20how%20prepared%20and%20confident%20you%20are.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BCouriers%20of%20bad%20tidings%20are%20often%20fearful%20that%20the%20messenger%20will%20get%20shot%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Sonnenfeld.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EYet%20being%20forthcoming%20can%20pay%20off.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20you're%20right%2C%20you%20could%20maybe%20save%20lives%20or%20save%20a%20company%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-to-give-negative-feedback-to-your-boss-2025-6%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2