3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EConsider%20a%20diversified%20portfolio%20with%20stocks%20and%20bonds%2C%20adjusting%20for%20risk%20tolerance.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3ESo%20you've%20just%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fclass-of-2025-commencement-speech-highlights-career-advice-college-graduates-2025-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Egraduated%20from%20college%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Congratulations!%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20an%20exciting%20time%20in%20your%20life%20as%20you%20get%20ready%20to%20enter%20the%20workforce.%20One%20of%20the%20great%20things%20about%20being%20at%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ffinance-careers-investment-banking-private-equity-hedge-funds-articles-videos-2025-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Estart%20of%20your%20career%20journey%3C%2Fa%3E%20is%20that%20you%20have%20ample%20time%20to%20figure%20out%20the%20path%20you%20want%20to%20take%20in%20life%20and%20where%20your%20passions%20lie.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETime%20is%20also%20your%20greatest%20asset%20when%20it%20comes%20to%20setting%20yourself%20up%20for%20a%20life%20of%20investing%20success.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThanks%20to%20the%20power%20of%20compounding%2C%20which%20Albert%20Einstein%20famously%20called%20the%20eighth%20wonder%20of%20the%20world%2C%20the%20earlier%20you%20start%20investing%2C%20the%20better.%20According%20to%20insurance%20firm%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fblog.massmutual.com%2Fretiring-investing%2Fsaving-retirement-20s%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EMass%20Mutual%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20a%2022-year-old%20who%20invests%20%24500%20a%20month%20will%20have%20%242%2C255%2C844%20by%20age%2065%2C%20assuming%20the%20stock%20market%20delivers%20an%20average%20annual%20return%20of%208%25.%20That%20number%20falls%20to%20%24972%2C542%20if%20one%20starts%20investing%20at%2032.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20investing%20isn't%20always%20easy%2C%20especially%20early%20on%20in%20your%20career%20when%20your%20earnings%20are%20lower.%20The%20process%20may%20also%20feel%20daunting%20and%20complicated%20if%20you%20haven't%20done%20it%20before.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETo%20put%20those%20fears%20to%20rest%2C%20we've%20come%20up%20with%20a%20step-by-step%20guide%20on%20how%20to%20best%20get%20your%20financial%20house%20in%20order%20so%20you'll%20thank%20yourself%20down%20the%20road.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22b1bb59fd-c168-4975-b26d-cc00485f6a78%5C%22%3ECome%20up%20with%20a%20budget%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThere's%20no%20one-size-fits-all%20approach%20for%20budgeting%2C%20so%20it's%20important%20to%20come%20up%20with%20a%20plan%20that%20works%20for%20you%2C%20said%20Melissa%20Cox%2C%20the%20Dallas-based%20owner%20of%20Future-Focused%20Wealth.%20Trying%20to%20keep%20up%20with%20someone%20who%20may%20have%20a%20different%20budget%20than%20you%20do%20is%20one%20of%20the%20most%20common%20mistakes%20she%20sees%20young%20people%20make.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BSo%20many%20people%20come%20out%20of%20school%20and%20they%20just%20go%20crazy%20spending%20money%2C%26quot%3B%20Cox%20said.%20%26quot%3BSocial%20media%20and%20everyone%20sees%20what%20everyone%20else%20is%20doing%20%E2%80%94%20don't%20fall%20into%20that.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20good%20rule%20of%20thumb%20is%20to%20set%20aside%2020%25%20of%20your%20pre-tax%20income%2C%20according%20to%20Bryan%20Kuderna%2C%20the%20founder%20of%20New%20Jersey-based%20Kuderna%20Financial%20Team.%20So%2C%20if%20your%20salary%20is%20%24100%2C000%2C%20you%20should%20be%20trying%20to%20save%20%2420%2C000%20a%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20again%2C%20the%20practical%20savings%20rate%20will%20vary%20from%20person%20to%20person.%20Many%20recent%20grads%20have%20student%20loans%20to%20tackle%2C%20so%20it's%20good%20to%20understand%20what%20your%20repayment%20options%20are%2C%20Cox%20said.%20Maybe%20forgiveness%20is%20possible%2C%20or%20lower%20monthly%20payments%20based%20on%20your%20income.%20Perhaps%20refinancing%20your%20loans%20will%20allow%20for%20more%20manageable%20payments.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFinally%2C%20it's%20important%20to%20keep%20yourself%20a%20priority%2C%20Cox%20said.%20For%20example%2C%20perhaps%20you%20really%20value%20traveling%20or%20shopping%20%E2%80%94%20it's%20good%20to%20set%20some%20money%20aside%20for%20those%20things%20as%20well.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%225596fdcf-b6ae-4a5f-9737-746d07e90db9%5C%22%3EBuild%20a%20buffer%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20you%20start%20working%2C%20it's%20smart%20to%20set%20up%20a%20retirement%20account%20like%20a%20401(k)%20or%20Roth%20IRA%20and%20start%20contributing%20right%20away.%20But%20we'll%20get%20to%20that%20in%20the%20next%20section.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20it%20comes%20to%20your%20money%20outside%20those%20accounts%2C%20the%20first%20thing%20you%20want%20to%20do%20%E2%80%94%20assuming%20you%20don't%20have%20credit-card%20debt%20%E2%80%94%20is%20build%20up%20a%20buffer%20of%20six%20months%20of%20living%20expenses%2C%20Kuderna%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20is%20because%20people%20in%20their%2020s%20often%20have%20big%20life%20events%20that%20they%20need%20the%20money%20for%2C%20he%20said.%20Having%20it%20in%20risky%20assets%20like%20stocks%20makes%20it%20vulnerable%20to%20downside%20in%20the%20near%20term.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20always%20say%20liquidity%20is%20huge%20for%20a%20young%20professional%2C%26quot%3B%20Kuderna%20said.%20%26quot%3BI%20might%20move%20out%2C%20I%20might%20have%20to%20get%20a%20new%20car%2C%20I%20might%20be%20getting%20engaged%2C%20married%2C%20a%20kid%20%E2%80%94%20all%20these%20things%20that%20can%20happen%20in%20your%2020s.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20you%20might%20not%20want%20your%20money%20invested%20in%20stocks%20right%20away%2C%20you%20also%20don't%20want%20to%20have%20it%20just%20sitting%20in%20a%20checking%20account.%20Instead%2C%20plug%20it%20into%20a%20high-yield%20savings%20account%20or%20a%20money%20market%20fund%20to%20collect%20a%20better%20yield%20while%20short-term%20interest%20rates%20are%20still%20high.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%229dd7784c-595f-429b-9d7e-82843ceeb801%5C%22%3EOpen%20multiple%20investment%20accounts%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EOK%2C%20now%20for%20the%20investment%20accounts.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFirst%2C%20make%20sure%20you%20have%20a%20Roth%20IRA%20or%20401(k)%20set%20up%20with%20your%20employer%20and%20are%20collecting%20their%20monthly%20minimum%20match.%20As%20of%202025%2C%20you%20can%20contribute%20up%20to%20%2423%2C500%20to%20a%20401(k)%20and%20%247%2C000%20to%20a%20Roth%20IRA.%20401(k)%20contributions%20are%20made%20with%20pre-tax%20money%3B%20the%20money%20is%20then%20taxed%20upon%20withdrawal.%20Roth%20IRA%20contributions%20are%20made%20with%20post-tax%20income%2C%20and%20eventual%20withdrawals%20are%20not%20taxed.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESetting%20these%20accounts%20up%20is%20important%20because%20the%20money%20comes%20straight%20out%20of%20your%20paychecks%20%E2%80%94%20it's%20like%20it%20never%20existed%2C%20and%20there's%20less%20of%20a%20temptation%20to%20spend%20it%20since%20withdrawals%20before%20you're%2059-and-a-half%20years%20old%20are%20penalized%20at%2010%25.%20Plus%2C%20you%20can%20take%20advantage%20of%20the%20tax%20benefits.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI'm%20huge%20on%20Roth%20options%2C%20especially%20for%20young%20people%2C%26quot%3B%20Kuderna%20said.%20%26quot%3BIf%20we%20can%20get%20tax-free%20growth%20for%20another%20four%20or%20five%20decades%2C%20that's%20worth%20its%20weight%20in%20gold.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOnce%20those%20are%20set%20up%2C%20open%20up%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Finvesting%2Fbest-investment-apps-for-beginners%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ebrokerage%20account%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20invest%20your%20excess%20savings.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EConsidering%20your%20cash%20savings%2C%20Kuderna%20said%20this%20is%20taking%20a%20three-pronged%20approach%3A%20having%20cash%20for%20the%20short-term%2C%20a%20brokerage%20account%20with%20stock%20investments%20for%20the%20medium-term%20(maybe%20a%20down%20payment%20for%20a%20house%20in%20five%2C%2010%2C%20or%2020%20years)%2C%20and%20retirement%20accounts%20for%20the%20long-term.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHaving%20a%20brokerage%20account%20for%20medium-term%20investments%20will%20allow%20you%20to%20capture%20potential%20market%20upside%20while%20not%20being%20subject%20to%20the%2010%25%20penalty%20of%20withdrawing%20money%20from%20a%20401(k)%20or%20Roth%20IRA%20early.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BYou%20don't%20want%20to%20neglect%20the%20mid-term%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BWhen%20you're%2040%20or%20you're%2050%20and%20you%20need%20money%2C%20you%20don't%20want%20to%20hit%20your%20retirement%20accounts%2C%20and%20you%20don't%20want%20to%20have%20it%20all%20just%20sitting%20in%20cash.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%223855ff32-aecf-408f-945e-f9015211f893%5C%22%3EDecide%20where%20to%20invest%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ENow%20that%20you%20have%20your%20accounts%20set%20up%2C%20it's%20time%20to%20decide%20where%20to%20invest.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20classic%20portfolio%20structure%20is%2060%25%20stocks%20and%2040%25%20bonds.%20Stocks%2C%20while%20riskier%2C%20offer%20greater%20upside%20potential.%20Meanwhile%2C%20bonds%20are%20supposed%20to%20act%20as%20a%20buffer%20to%20stock%20market%20volatility%20by%20protecting%20your%20capital%2C%20producing%20a%20steady%20yield%2C%20and%20appreciating%20during%20times%20of%20economic%20distress.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20since%20you're%20in%20your%2020s%2C%20you%20might%20consider%20allocating%20even%20more%20of%20your%20money%20to%20stocks%20since%20you%20can%20likely%20withstand%20more%20volatility%2C%20according%20to%20Chris%20Chen%2C%20the%20founder%20of%20Insight%20Financial%20Strategists.%20He%20said%20an%2080%2F20%20portfolio%20may%20be%20more%20appropriate.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHow%20you%20allocate%20money%20in%20your%20medium-term%20and%20long-term%20investment%20accounts%20may%20look%20different%2C%20however.%20For%20your%20401(k)%20or%20Roth%20IRA%2C%20one%20simple%20way%20to%20invest%20for%20the%20long%20term%20is%20by%20buying%20a%20target-date%20fund.%20For%20example%2C%20you%20might%20choose%20the%20Vanguard%20Target%20Retirement%202065%20Fund%20(%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Finvestor.vanguard.com%2Finvestment-products%2Fmutual-funds%2Fprofile%2Fvlxvx%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EVLXVX%3C%2Fa%3E)%20or%20the%20State%20Street%20Target%20Retirement%202070%20Fund%20(%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ssga.com%2Fus%2Fen%2Finstitutional%2Fmf%2Fstate-street-target-retirement-2070-fund-class-i-ssgqx%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ESSGQX%3C%2Fa%3E).%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThese%20funds%20automatically%20adjust%20your%20allocations%20to%20stocks%20and%20bonds%20as%20you%20age.%20As%20you%20start%20to%20approach%20retirement%2C%20the%20percentage%20of%20your%20money%20in%20bonds%20starts%20to%20increase%20to%20preserve%20your%20capital.%20Right%20now%2C%20the%20Vanguard%202065%20fund%20has%2053.1%25%20of%20its%20assets%20in%20the%20Vanguard%20Total%20Stock%20Market%20Index%20Fund%2C%20which%20is%20made%20up%20of%20US%20stocks%3B%2037.5%25%20of%20the%20fund%20is%20in%20the%20Vanguard%20Total%20International%20Stock%20Index%20Fund%3B%206.5%25%20is%20in%20US%20bonds%3B%20and%202.9%25%20is%20in%20international%20bonds.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EExpense%20ratios%2C%20or%20the%20fees%20that%20certain%20funds%20charge%2C%20are%20also%20something%20to%20keep%20in%20mind.%20The%20Vanguard%20Target%20Retirement%20funds%2C%20for%20example%2C%20have%20a%20fairly%20cheap%20expense%20ratio%20of%200.08%25%20a%20year.%20The%20cheapest%20S%26amp%3BP%20500%20index%20fund%20is%20the%20Fidelity%20500%20Index%20Fund%20(%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmarkets.businessinsider.com%2Ffunds%2Ffidelity-500-index-fund-us3159117502%3FmiRedirects%3D1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EFXAIX%3C%2Fa%3E)%20at%200.015%25.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20your%20medium-term%20investments%2C%20you%20should%20assess%20your%20risk-tolerance%20and%20timeline.%20Stock%20valuations%20are%20high%20at%20the%20moment%2