ives%20of%20Those%20Who%20Fix%2C%20Reuse%20%26amp%3B%20Reinvent%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EIt%20was%20a%20Sunday%20morning%20in%20May%20when%20I%20set%20out%20on%20a%20photo%20walk%20with%20my%20best%20friend%20through%20the%20old%20lanes%20of%20Lucknow.%20Having%20recently%20relocated%2C%20this%20was%20my%20first%20time%20back%20in%20the%20old%20city%20and%20just%20the%20thought%20of%20seeing%20its%20rustic%20monuments%2C%20crumbling%20bricks%2C%20and%20fading%20paint%20brought%20back%20memories%20of%20a%20slower%20time%20%E2%80%94%20a%20time%20when%20people%20valued%20what%20they%20had%20and%20chose%20to%20repair%2C%20not%20replace.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAt%20six%20in%20the%20morning%2C%20the%20shops%20in%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthebetterindia.com%2F431994%2Flucknow-bioscope-sanatkada-begum-akhtar%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ELucknow%E2%80%99s%20%3Cem%3EChowk%20Bazaar%3C%2Fem%3E%20%3C%2Fa%3Ewere%20still%20shuttered%20as%20we%20set%20off%20on%20our%20little%20adventure%2C%20joined%20by%20a%20bunch%20of%20like-minded%20folks%2C%20all%20curious%20and%20eager%20to%20freeze%20time%20through%20our%20lenses.%20As%20we%20walked%2C%20our%20organiser%20shared%20stories%20about%20the%20streets%2C%20including%20one%20about%20%3Cem%3EChor%20Bazaar%20(Thieves%E2%80%99%20Market)%20%3C%2Fem%3Enear%20Victoria%20Street.%20He%20told%20us%20it%20was%20once%20called%20%3Cem%3EShahi%20Bazaar%20(Royal%20Market)%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20a%20place%20where%20people%20still%20buy%20old%20clothes%2C%20second-hand%20watches%2C%20and%20even%20get%20their%20transistors%20repaired.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThat%20moment%20reminded%20me%20of%20how%20deeply%20ingrained%3Cem%3E%20jugaad%20%E2%80%94%3C%2Fem%3E%20India%E2%80%99s%20way%20of%20making%20do%20with%20what%E2%80%99s%20available%20%E2%80%94%20is%20in%20our%20culture.%20My%20mind%20drifted%20to%20memories%20of%20my%20mother%20taking%20my%20worn-out%20shoes%20to%20the%20%3Cem%3Emochi%20(co