could%20be%20much%20higher%2C%20given%20that%20many%20people%20don't%20alert%20the%20FTC%20when%20scammed.%20Fake%20package%20delivery%20was%20the%20most%20common%20scam%2C%20but%20the%20No.%202%20was%20job%20offers%20%E2%80%94%20texts%20from%20purported%20recruiters%20either%20offering%20positions%20at%20well-known%20companies%20or%20promising%20big%20bucks%20in%20exchange%20for%20doing%20online%20tasks%20that%20seem%20relatively%20mundane.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20are%20definitely%20seeing%20both%20a%20growth%20in%20reported%20losses%20to%20text%20scams%20and%20also%20a%20growth%20in%20reported%20losses%20to%20job%20scams%2C%26quot%3B%20says%20Kati%20Daffan%2C%20an%20attorney%20for%20the%20FTC%20in%20its%20Bureau%20of%20Consumer%20Protection.%20%26quot%3BReported%20losses%20to%20job%20scams%20increased%20more%20than%20three%20times%20between%202020%20and%202023.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENow%2C%20the%20flood%20of%20job%20scams%20could%20get%20even%20worse.%20There%20is%20increased%20opportunity%20for%20dupers%3A%20The%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Famerica-cracking-job-market-layoffs-unemployment-recession-tariffs-2025-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Elabor%20market%20is%20getting%20rockier%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20Americans%20are%20increasingly%20on%20edge%20about%20their%20finances%2C%20and%20many%20people%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fremote-hybrid-jobs-rto-jpmorgan-amazon-2025-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ereally%20want%20to%20work%20remotely%3C%2Fa%3E.%20At%20the%20same%20time%2C%20the%20means%20of%20cranking%20out%20these%20texts%20is%20getting%20more%20sophisticated%3A%20AI%20makes%20scam%20texts%20easier%20to%20craft%20in%20ways%20that%20seem%20plausible%20and%20realistic.%20The%20overall%20result%20is%20that%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fred-flags-that-remote-job-could-be-a-scam-2025-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eunsuspecting%20job%20seekers%20may%20become%20even%20more%20susceptible%20to%20hoaxes%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20likely%20that%20as%20unemployment%20increases%20and%20more%20people%20are%20worried%20about%20the%20economic%20uncertainty%2C%20if%20the%20scams%20aren't%20necessarily%20increasing%2C%20the%20likelihood%20that%20people%20might%20fall%20for%20them%20will%20be%2C%26quot%3B%20says%20Selena%20Larson%2C%20a%20staff%20threat%20researcher%20at%20Proofpoint%2C%20a%20cybersecurity%20company.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20way%20scam%20texts%20work%20is%20pretty%20straightforward%3A%20You%20get%20a%20message%20out%20of%20nowhere%20about%20a%20supposed%20thrilling%20work%20opportunity.%20It%20may%20come%20from%20a%20phone%20number%2C%20or%20it's%20from%20an%20official-looking%20email%20address.%20The%20offer%20seems%20enticing%2C%20albeit%20somewhat%20unrealistic%20given%20how%20jobs%20and%20money%20usually%20go%20%E2%80%94%20it%20may%20promise%20a%20super-high%20salary%20for%20just%20a%20couple%20of%20hours%20a%20day%20of%20menial%20online%20work.%20It%20can%20also%20come%20with%20some%20weird%20facets%2C%20such%20as%20conducting%20interviews%20entirely%20via%20text%2C%20promising%20to%20pay%20in%20crypto%2C%20or%20asking%20you%20to%20pay%20them%20before%20they%20pay%20you.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEva%20Velasquez%2C%20the%20CEO%20of%20the%20Identity%20Theft%20Resource%20Center%2C%20a%20nonprofit%2C%20says%20her%20organization%20saw%20a%20big%20bump%20in%20job%20scam%20reports%20in%202023%20that%20took%20them%20by%20surprise.%20Since%20then%2C%20the%20number%20has%20ebbed%20and%20flowed%2C%20but%20the%20scams%20are%20here%20to%20stay.%20%26quot%3BThey%20are%20very%20lucrative.%20They%20can%20capture%20not%20only%20your%20data%20but%20often%20your%20money%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EScammers%20get%20people%20to%20hand%20over%20personal%20information%20that%20would%20be%20par%20for%20the%20course%20for%20a%20legit%20hiring%20process%20%E2%80%94%20Social%20Security%20numbers%2C%20pictures%20of%20their%20driver's%20licenses%20and%20passports%2C%20bank%20account%20numbers.%20That%20information%20can%20be%20used%20to%20try%20to%20steal%20people's%20identities%20and%20for%20other%20nefarious%20ends.%20And%20for%20someone%20who%20really%20wants%20a%20new%20job%2C%20the%20mundanity%20of%20the%20requests%20can%20be%20deceiving.%20%26quot%3BThat%20I%20think%20is%20why%20it's%20confusing%20to%20people%20is%20when%20you%20have%20a%20legitimate%20offer%20and%20you%20do%20start%20with%20an%20employer%2C%20they%20do%20need%20that%20information%2C%26quot%3B%20Velasquez%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhat's%20not%20so%20normal%20is%20job%20scammers%20asking%20victims%20to%20kick%20in%20their%20own%20money.%20The%20trick%20goes%20like%20this%3A%20After%20supposedly%20hiring%20someone%20or%20getting%20far%20enough%20in%20the%20process%2C%20the%20scammer%20will%20send%20someone%20a%20check%20and%20ask%20them%20to%20buy%20work-related%20equipment%20with%20it%2C%20such%20as%20a%20printer%20or%20office%20supplies.%20But%20the%20check%20will%20be%20for%20more%20money%20than%20the%20stuff%20costs%2C%20so%20they'll%20ask%20the%20person%20to%20send%20the%20difference%20back.%20Later%2C%20the%20check%20bounces%2C%20and%20the%20person%20is%20out%20of%20the%20money%20they%20spent%20on%20the%20equipment%20and%20sent%20to%20the%20scammer%20%E2%80%94%20and%2C%20potentially%2C%20in%20hot%20water%20for%20depositing%20a%20fake%20check.%20They%20may%20also%20ask%20people%20to%20buy%20gift%20cards%20or%20make%20payments%20to%20fake%20vendors%20who%20are%20in%20on%20the%20scam.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDaffan%2C%20from%20the%20FTC%2C%20says%20it%20has%20specifically%20seen%20a%20spike%20in%20task%20scams%2C%20in%20which%20consumers%20are%20asked%20to%20complete%20little%20activities%20online%2C%20such%20as%20liking%20videos%20or%20rating%20products%20on%20an%20app%20or%20platform%2C%20to%20earn%20commission.%20The%20texts%20say%20the%20activity%20is%20for%20%26quot%3Bproduct%20boosting%26quot%3B%20or%20%26quot%3Bapp%20optimization%2C%26quot%3B%20which%20can%20sound%20realistic.%20%26quot%3BBut%20then%20once%20people%20start%20doing%20this%20work%2C%20there's%20a%20whole%20system%20designed%20to%20trick%20them%20to%20actually%20pay%20money%20into%20the%20app%2C%20and%20eventually%2C%20they'll%20end%20up%20losing%20money%20and%20never%20being%20given%20any%20of%20the%20money%20that%20they%20were%20promised%2C%26quot%3B%20Daffan%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20as%20much%20as%20many%20people%20like%20to%20feel%20that%20they'd%20never%20fall%20for%20a%20scam%2C%20we're%20all%20susceptible%20to%20them%2C%20to%20some%20extent.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20relies%20on%20this%20concept%20of%20social%20engineering%20and%20the%20hackers%20being%20very%20compelling.%20They%20make%20you%20feel%20something%2C%20they%20make%20you%20feel%20excited%2C%26quot%3B%20Larson%20says.%20%26quot%3BThey%20make%20you%20feel%20like%20you%20want%20to%20be%20a%20part%20of%20this%20ecosystem%2C%20that%20this%20job%20is%20a%20great%20opportunity%20that%20you%20don't%20want%20to%20lose.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20stereotypical%20victim%20of%20a%20fraudster%20is%20an%20older%20person%20%E2%80%94%20your%20grandmother%20on%20the%20phone%20with%20someone%20who%20claims%20to%20be%20from%20Publishers%20Clearing%20House%2C%20telling%20her%20she's%20won%20a%20million%20dollars%20but%20has%20to%20kick%20in%20some%20of%20her%20own%20cash%20first.%20But%20in%20the%20modern%20world%2C%20that%20stereotype%20is%20out%20of%20date%2C%20including%20when%20it%20comes%20to%20job%20text%20scams%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgen-z-loses-more-money-to-online-scams-than-boomers-2024-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EA%20lot%20of%20young%20people%20take%20the%20bait%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGen%20Zers%20and%20millennials%20are%20used%20to%20doing%20everything%20online%2C%20even%20making%20major%20life%20decisions.%20Nothing%2C%20whether%20it's%20booking%20a%20vacation%2C%20renting%20an%20apartment%2C%20or%20paying%20a%20friend%20back%2C%20feels%20like%20a%20%26quot%3Bbig%20screen%26quot%3B%20task%20anymore%2C%20let%20alone%20a%20do-this-in-person%20one.%20It's%20all%20on%20the%20small%20screen.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI'm%20a%20Gen%20Xer.%20For%20me%2C%20someone%20conducting%20very%20serious%20business%20over%20text%20just%20doesn't%20resonate%20with%20me%2C%26quot%3B%20Velasquez%20says.%20%26quot%3BFor%20young%20people%2C%20they're%20like%2C%20we%20do%20everything%20over%20text.%20It%20doesn't%20raise%20alarm%20bells.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EYounger%20people%20are%20more%20accustomed%20to%20the%20idea%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgen-z-hustle-generation-jobs-work-side-hustle-freelance-2023-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eside%20hustles%3C%2Fa%3E.%20They're%20in%20the%20hunt%20for%20extra%20cash%2C%20especially%20if%20they%20can%20earn%20it%20with%20little%20effort%20online%2C%20and%20%26quot%3Blike%20these%20videos%20for%20money%26quot%3B%20may%20not%20seem%20that%20abnormal%20to%20them%20in%20a%20world%20where%20%26quot%3Bpost%20videos%20on%20TikTok%20for%20money%26quot%3B%20is%20an%20aspired-to%20reality.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGen%20Z%20also%20faces%20an%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdoge-damage-gen-z-careers-tech-layoffs-job-market-hiring-2025-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eespecially%20tough%20job%20market%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Between%20tech%20layoffs%20and%20federal%20government%20job%20cuts%2C%20many%20avenues%20they%20may%20have%20pursued%20have%20dried%20up.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Femployees-stuck-job-search-hiring-work-trump-tariffs-2025-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ECompanies%20aren't%20hiring%3C%2Fa%3E%20the%20way%20they%20were%20a%20few%20years%20ago%2C%20and%20people%20with%20jobs%20aren't%20quitting.%20That%20can%20specifically%20affect%20younger%20people%20looking%20to%20get%20a%20foot%20in%20the%20door%20%E2%80%94%20if%20nobody's%20going%20out%2C%20they%20can't%20get%20in.%20The%20result%3A%20a%20generation%20that's%20extra%20prone%20to%20falling%20into%20scams%20offering%20jobs%20and%20side-hustle%20cash.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BYou%20look%20at%20the%20Gen%20Zs%20and%20the%20younger%20millennials%20and%20they%20just%20click%2C%20click%2C%20click%2C%20click%2C%20click%2C%20click%2C%26quot%3B%20says%20Alex%20Quilici%2C%20the%20CEO%20of%20YouMail%2C%20a%20service%20that%20helps%20block%20scam%20texts%20and%20calls.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20I%20reported%20this%20story%2C%20I%20became%20increasingly%20alarmed%20about%20job%20scam%20texts.%20If%20the%20labor%20market%20is%20worsening%2C%20meaning%20more%20people%20are%20going%20to%20fall%20for%20this%20stuff%2C%20shouldn't%20we%20be%20doing%20more%20to%20stop%20it%3F%20On%20the%20list%20of%20a%20million%20worries%2C%20I'd%20really%20rather%20not%20add%20%26quot%3Bmy%20niece%20got%20bamboozled%20out%20of%20%241%2C000%20because%20of%20some%20click%20farm%20scam%26quot%3B%20to%20the%20list.%20It%20turns%20out%20that%20doing%20something%20about%20this%20is%20hard.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20I%20ask%20Kate%20Griffin%2C%20with%20the%20Aspen%20Institute's%20Financial%20Security%20Program%2C%20who's%20responsible%20for%20clamping%20down%20on%20scam%20texts%2C%20she%20tells%20me%2C%20%26quot%3BThat's%20the%20problem.%26quot%3B%20It's%20sort%20of%20everyone's%20job%2C%20which%20also%20means%20it's%20sort%20of%20no%20one's%20job.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BA%20lot%20of%20people%20have%20a%20component%20part%20of%20it%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20says.%20%26quot%3BThere's%20a%20part%20of%20the%20FBI%20that%20goes%20after%20this.%20There's%20a%20part%20of%20the%20Treasury%20Department%20that%20is%20focused%20on%20the%20anti-money-laundering%20part%20of%20it.%20The%20FTC%2C%20of%20course%2C%20holds%20their%20component%20of%20it%2C%20but%20there's%20not%20a%20single%20coordinating%20entity%20to%20say%2C%20'What%20is%20our%20national%20approach%20to%20fighting%20this%3F'%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20far%20as%20how%20the%20private%20sector%20can%20combat%20this%2C%20it's%20complicated%2C%20too.%20Griffin%20explains%20that%20while%20telecommunications%20companies%20are%20the%20infrastructure%20layer%2C%20they%20don't%20necessarily%20have%20the%20ability%20to%20know%20what's%20inside%20messages.%20She%20notes%20that%20CTIA%2C%20a%20trade%20association%20that%20represents%20the%20wireless%20industry%2C%20has%20a%20%26quot%3B%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ctia.org%2Fctia-secure-messaging-initiative%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esecure%20messaging%20initiative%3C%2Fa%3E%26quot%3B%20whose%20goal%20is%20to%20put%20a%20stop%20to%20unwanted%20or%20illegal%20text%20messages.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBesides%20its%20app%20that%20lets%20consumers%20block%20unwanted%20communications%20from%20spammers%20and%20scammers%2C%20Quilici's%20YouMail%20also%20collects%20data%20to%20alert%20phone%20carriers%20of%20scams%20and%20bad%20actors.%20Still%2C%20it's%20hard%20for%20companies%20to%20get%20their%20arms%20around%20the%20problem%20%E2%80%94%20scammers%20are%20savvy%2C%20and%20the%20business%20incentives%20to%20crack%20down%20on%20them%20aren't%20particularly%20compelling.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20you%20wanted%20to%20try%20to%20stop%20it%2C%20you'd%20have%20to%20make%20it%20really%2C%20really%20difficult%20for%20anybody%20to%20get%20a%20phone%20number%2C%26quot%3B%20Quilici%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETexting%20and%20calling%20cost%20next%20to%20nothing.%20Making%20communications%20more%20expensive%20would%20make%20scamming%20less%20lucrative%2C%20but%20it%20would%20also%20make%20basic%20functions%20pricier%20for%20everyone%20else.%20Companies%20(or%20the%20government)%20could%20implement%20know-your-customer%20laws%2C%20as%20banks%20have%2C%20so%20carriers%20have%20to%20know%20whom%20they're%20giving%20a%20number%20to%2C%20but%20that%20would%20be%20onerous%2C%20too.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThere's%20a%20big%20tension%20between%20their%20desire%20to%20sell%20services%20and%20quickly%20and%20stopping%20fraud%2C%26quot%3B%20Quilici%20says.%20%26quot%3BI%20don't%20view%20the%20carriers%20as%20bad%20guys.%20I%20view%20them%20as%20having%20a%20business%20problem.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20unwillingness%20of%20the%20government%20and%20phone%20carriers%20to%20make%20a%20concerted%20effort%20against%20scam%20texts%20puts%20a%20lot%20of%20onus%20on%20individual%20consumers%20to%20try%20to%20protect%20themselves%2C%20which%20is%20not%20an%20easy%20task.%20A%20lot%20of%20these%20scams%20look%20realistic%20%E2%80%94%20ChatGPT%20makes%20it%20easier%20to%20write%20a%20scam%2C%20meaning%20the%20grammar%20mistakes%20that%20might%20have%20set%20off%20some%20spidey%20senses%20are%20less%20likely%20to%20appear.%20These%20scams%20don't%20just%20take%20place%20via%20text%3B%20they%20can%20also%20come%20in%20emails%20or%20even%20in%20social%20media%20messages%20on%20platforms%20such%20as%20LinkedIn%2C%20where%20contact%20from%20a%20recruiter%20would%20seem%20quite%20normal.%20And%20they%20often%20invoke%20big-name%20companies%20that%20people%20would%20like%20to%20work%20for%2C%20which%20may%20increase%20the%20likelihood%20that%20someone%20falls%20for%20a%20trick.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhat's%20one%20to%20do%20in%20this%20scenario%3F%20First%2C%20scrutinize%20where%20the%20text%20came%20from.%20(Is%20it%20a%20weird%20email%20address%20or%20a%20foreign%20phone%20number%3F%20Though%20scammers%20can%20make%20those%20look%20plausible%2C%20too.)%20Next%2C%20do%20a%20deep%20reading%20of%20the%20message%20itself%2C%20checking%20whether%20the%20grammar%20is%20right%20and%20whether%20the%20offer%20seems%20too%20good%20to%20be%20true.%20A%20six-figure%20job%20for%20clicking%20boxes%20on%20an%20app%20sounds%20lovely%2C%20but%20it's%20also%20not%20a%20thing%20that%20exists.%20Mention%20of%20pay%20in%20crypto%20is%20a%20red%20flag%2C%20as%20are%20interviews%20via%20text.%20If%20the%20alleged%20employer%20asks%20you%20for%20money%2C%20that's%20a%20no-no.%20As%20a%20general%20rule%2C%20you%20shouldn't%20have%20to%20pay%20money%20to%20make%20money.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BOur%20advice%20is%20never%20click%20on%20links%20or%20respond%20to%20unexpected%20texts%20or%20WhatsApp%20messages%20or%20other%20messages%20about%20jobs.%20Real%20employers%20will%20never%20contact%20you%20that%20way%2C%26quot%3B%20Daffan%20says.%20She%20asks%20people%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22http%3A%2F%2Freportfraud.ftc.gov%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ereport%20fraud%20to%20the%20FTC%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20you%20do%20think%20a%20job%20offer%20could%20be%20legitimate%2C%20see%20whether%20you%20can%20find%20the%20listing%20online%20%E2%80%94%20and%20make%20sure%20it's%20real%20and%20matches%20on%20details%20such%20as%20salary%20and%20location.%20People%20can%20also%20just%20contact%20the%20prospective%20employer%20directly%20to%20find%20out%20if%20it%20is%20a%20fake.%20And%20if%20you%20do%20get%20scammed%20out%20of%20money%2C%20contact%20your%20bank%20immediately%20and%20try%20to%20get%20the%20money%20back.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EUltimately%2C%20Quilici%20says%2C%20the%20best%20advice%20is%20to%20slow%20down.%20There's%20no%20need%20to%20respond%20to%20that%20job%20offer%20text%20right%20away.%20Larson%20echoes%20the%20point.%20%26quot%3BIf%20they're%20trying%20to%20rush%20you%2C%20they're%20trying%20to%20hire%20you%2C%20and%20they%20ask%20to%20be%20paid%20for%20something%2C%20that's%20all%20red%20flags%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20says.%20Anyone%20who's%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmultiple-job-interviews-a-pain-but-also-benefit-workers-2024-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Einterviewed%20for%20a%20job%3C%2Fa%3E%20lately%20knows%20that%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmultiple-job-interviews-a-pain-but-also-benefit-workers-2024-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ethe%20process%20can%20drag%20on%20for%20a%20wildly%20long%20time%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOverall%2C%20the%20good%20news%20is%20that%20as%20time%20goes%20on%20and%20more%20people%20learn%20about%20scams%2C%20the%20more%20we%20collectively%20become%20inoculated%20to%20different%20tactics%20and%20hoaxes.%20People%20were%20highly%20susceptible%20to%20email%20scams%20when%20they%20first%20got%20email%20addresses.%20Now%2C%20you%20still%20hear%20about%20them%2C%20but%20they're%20a%20lot%20less%20common%2C%20and%20most%20people%20have%20an%20easier%20time%20spotting%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20meantime%2C%20the%20bad%20news%20is%20that%20a%20tougher%20labor%20market%20means%20we%20may%20not%20have%20time%20for%20this%20natural%20collective%20education%20to%20happen.%20When%20people%20are%20anxious%20about%20money%20and%20work%2C%20they're%20likelier%20to%20have%20blind%20spots%20that%20scammers%20know%20how%20to%20exploit.%20If%20you're%20on%20month%20five%20of%20the%20job%20search%20and%20worried%20about%20how%20you're%20going%20to%20pay%20rent%2C%20you'll%20probably%20reply%20to%20that%20text%20faster%20than%20you%20would%20under%20normal%20circumstances.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BOne%20of%20the%20reasons%20that%20job%20scams%20are%20flourishing%20is%20that%20many%20people%20do%20want%20to%20work%20extra%20and%20make%20extra%20income%2C%20and%20they're%20looking%20for%20an%20opportunity%20to%20do%20that%2C%26quot%3B%20Daffan%20says.%20%26quot%3BAnd%20scammers%20know%20that%2C%20and%20so%20they%20know%20there's%20a%20big%20market%20out%20there%20if%20they%20can%20have%20a%20convincing%20job%20scam.%20And%2C%20unfortunately%2C%20that%20is%20the%20case.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fauthor%2Femily-stewart%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3EEmily%20Stewart%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E%20is%20a%20senior%20correspondent%20at%20Business%20Insider%2C%20writing%20about%20business%20and%20the%20economy.%3C%2Fem%3E