0ways%20to%20educate%20their%20kids.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3ESome%20education%20policy%20analysts%20said%20the%20lack%20of%20regulations%20for%20microschools%20raises%20concerns.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EMary%20Jo%20Fairhead%20felt%20that%20something%20was%20missing%20at%20the%20South%20Dakota%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Epublic%20schools%20where%20she%20taught%20for%20over%20a%20decade%2C%20so%20she%20quit%20and%20started%20one%20in%20her%20home.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20main%20challenge%20she's%20working%20to%20solve%20at%20her%20school%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fonwardlearning.org%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EOnward%20Learning%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20which%20launched%20in%202022%2C%20is%20individual%20attention.%20She%20said%20each%20teacher%20has%20about%2010%20students.%20Schools%20nationally%2C%20by%20contrast%2C%20have%20an%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nea.org%2Fresource-library%2Feducator-pay-and-student-spending-how-does-your-state-rank%2Fteacher%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eaverage%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%2015%20students%20per%20instructor.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20know%20every%20one%20of%20our%20kids%20on%20a%20very%20personal%20basis%2C%26quot%3B%20Fairhead%20said.%20%26quot%3BI%20know%20when%20they%20walk%20through%20the%20door%20if%20something's%20off%2C%20and%20I%20need%20to%20check%20in%20with%20them.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOnward%20Learning%20is%20part%20of%20the%20growing%20%26quot%3Bmicroschool%26quot%3B%20movement%20in%20the%20US.%20These%20schools%20have%20fewer%20than%2020%20students%20total%20on%20average%20and%20tend%20to%20employ%20an%20alternative%20learning%20environment%20that%20focuses%20on%20personalized%20lessons%20for%20each%20student.%20Demand%20for%20them%20is%20growing%20due%20to%20parents'%20desires%20to%20have%20a%20greater%20say%20in%20their%20kids'%20educations%20and%20have%20more%20options%20beyond%20the%20public%20schools%20in%20their%20district.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETheir%20popularity%20comes%20as%20the%20Trump%20administration%20is%20seeking%20to%20expand%20school%20voucher%20programs%20and%20has%20proposed%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftrump-vouchers-school-choice-block-grants-public-funding-private-education-2025-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eredirecting%20federal%20funds%3C%2Fa%3E%20from%20public%20schools%20to%20private%20schools%2C%20which%20could%20boost%20microschools'%20resources.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECritics%20worry%20that%20the%20category%20is%20poorly%20defined%20%E2%80%94%20it%20could%20encompass%20a%20homeschool%20or%20a%20group%20facilitated%20by%20a%20teacher%20in%20a%20church%2C%20allowing%20for%20minimal%20state%20and%20federal%20regulation.%20Microschool%20advocates%20said%20kids%20learn%20best%20when%20education%20is%20tailored%20to%20best%20suit%20their%20needs.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20my%20opinion%20that%20this%20type%20of%20learning%20could%20be%20beneficial%20for%20any%20child%2C%20but%20especially%20those%20kids%20that%20just%20need%20a%20little%20more%20space%2C%20either%20space%20to%20learn%2C%20space%20to%20run%2C%20and%20just%20a%20little%20less%20pressure%2C%26quot%3B%20Fairhead%20said.%20%26quot%3BIf%20you're%20the%20type%20of%20parent%20who%20wants%20a%20very%20structured%20day%2C%20lots%20of%20testing%2C%20and%20all%20of%20that%2C%20then%20my%20type%20of%20school%20is%20probably%20not%20the%20right%20fit.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22646919ba-148c-4699-aca1-f523043e6456%5C%22%3E'A%20new%20version%20of%20a%20one-room%20schoolhouse'%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EGiven%20the%20lack%20of%20definition%2C%20it's%20difficult%20to%20predict%20the%20number%20of%20students%20enrolled%20in%20a%20microschool%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Eat%20any%20given%20time.%20The%20RAND%20Corporation%2C%20a%20nonpartisan%20research%20organization%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.rand.org%2Fpubs%2Fresearch_reports%2FRRA3698-1.html%23document-details%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esaid%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20a%20March%20report%20that%20%26quot%3Bthe%20best%20currently%20available%20estimate%26quot%3B%20for%20the%20number%20of%20kids%20enrolled%20in%20a%20microschool%20full-time%20is%20between%201%20million%20and%202%20million%2C%20with%20%26quot%3Bmany%20more%26quot%3B%20enrolled%20part-time.%20Some%20microschools%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.americanprogress.org%2Farticle%2Fthe-importance-of-holding-microschools-accountable%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Epartner%3C%2Fa%3E%20with%20religious%20institutions%20for%20funding%20and%20other%20resources.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFairhead%20said%20that%20her%20school%20enrolled%2012%20kids%20in%20its%20first%20year%2C%20and%20she%20just%20finished%20the%20third%20school%20year%20with%2037%20students%20from%20kindergarten%20through%208th%20grade%20and%20a%20%26quot%3Bpretty%20long%26quot%3B%20waitlist.%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EThe%20days%20are%20typically%20structured%20with%20a%20few%20hours%20of%20learning%20core%20subjects%20in%20the%20morning%2C%20like%20science%20and%20math%2C%20and%20the%20rest%20of%20the%20day%20is%20focused%20on%20%26quot%3Bexperiential%20learning%2C%26quot%3B%20like%20art%2C%20music%2C%20and%20outdoor%20activities.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShe%20also%20incorporates%20Lakota%20language%20%E2%80%94%20the%20indigenous%20language%20of%20the%20reservation%20near%20the%20school%20%E2%80%94%20into%20the%20students'%20curriculum.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20a%20child's%20struggling%20and%20they%20need%20something%20more%20personalized%2C%20we%20find%20it%20for%20them%2C%26quot%3B%20Fairhead%20said.%20%26quot%3BOr%20if%20they're%20excelling%20and%20they%20need%20something%20that's%20going%20to%20challenge%20them%20more%2C%20we%20find%20that%20for%20them.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221440%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Children%20at%20Onward%20Learning%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F683e12f86ffb6822ec61ebdc%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221080%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EFairhead's%20microschool%20dedicates%20part%20of%20the%20school%20day%20to%20experiential%20learning.%3Cp%3ECourtesy%20of%20Mary%20Jo%20Fairhead%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EInterest%20in%20microschools%20started%20to%20grow%20during%20the%20pandemic%20as%20families%20looked%20for%20ways%20to%20keep%20students%20together%20while%20schools%20were%20closed%2C%20Paige%20Shoemaker%20DeMio%2C%20a%20senior%20analyst%20for%20K-12%20education%20policy%20at%20the%20left-leaning%20Center%20for%20American%20Progress%2C%20told%20BI.%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EShe%20called%20it%20%26quot%3Ba%20new%20version%20of%20a%20one-room%20schoolhouse.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20National%20Microschooling%20Center%20%E2%80%94%20a%20nonprofit%20that%20works%20to%20advance%20the%20microschool%20movement%20%E2%80%94%20released%20an%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2F22424203.fs1.hubspotusercontent-na1.net%2Fhubfs%2F22424203%2FFinal%25202025%2520Sector%2520Analysis%2520Website.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eanalysis%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20the%20sector%20in%20May.%20Using%20data%20from%20interviews%20and%20online%20questionnaires%20with%20800%20microschools%20across%20all%2050%20states%20and%20the%20District%20of%20Columbia%2C%20the%20analysis%20said%20that%2074%25%20of%20microschools%20have%20annual%20tuition%20and%20fees%20at%20or%20below%20%2410%2C000.%20It%20also%20said%20that%2041%25%20of%20microschools%20rely%20on%20state-provided%20school%20choice%20funds%20to%20operate.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFairhead%20said%20that%20she%20partners%20with%20the%20local%20tribe%20for%20funding.%20She%20also%20received%20a%20%24200%2C000%20grant%20as%20a%20semifinalist%20of%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fstaging.yassprize.org%2Fabout%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EYass%20Prize%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20founded%20by%20billionaire%20Jeff%20Yass%20to%20award%20high-impact%20education%20initiatives.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%225707%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Onward%20Learning%20microschool%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F683e1224ca50259add4d7a0b%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223805%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EFairhead's%20microschool%20enrolled%2037%20students%20in%20the%20most%20recent%20school%20year.%3Cp%3ECourtesy%20of%20Mary%20Jo%20Fairhead%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EDon%20Soifer%2C%20CEO%20of%20the%20National%20Microschooling%20Center%2C%20told%20BI%20that%20the%20majority%20of%20microschool%20founders%20and%20teachers%20also%20have%20certified%20teaching%20experience.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BMicroschool%20leaders%20come%20from%20a%20background%20as%20experienced%20educators%20themselves%20who%20are%20excited%20at%20the%20opportunity%20for%20professional%20growth%20in%20no%20longer%20being%20bound%20by%20the%20requirements%20of%20the%20rigidities%20of%20a%20public%20school%20system%2C%26quot%3B%20Soifer%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESoifer%20added%20that%20the%20goal%20of%20microschools%20is%20not%20to%20replace%20the%20public%20school%20system.%20Rather%2C%20it's%20to%20give%20families%20another%20option%20where%20their%20kids%20can%20be%20in%20a%20much%20smaller%20setting%2C%20and%20parents%20can%20be%20more%20clued%20into%20what%20their%20child%20is%20doing%20on%20a%20day-to-day%20basis.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20all%20have%20friends%20who%20are%20working%20in%20the%20public%20schools%2C%20making%20important%20progress%20on%20improving%20them%2C%20and%20more%20power%20to%20them%20for%20having%20the%20patience%20to%20do%20that%2C%26quot%3B%20Soifer%20said%2C%20adding%20that%20he%20spent%20years%20doing%20the%20same.%20%26quot%3BBut%20there%20are%20families%20that%20can't%20wait%2020%20years%2C%2025%20years%20for%20the%20public%20schools%20to%20make%20the%20improvements%20that%20are%20going%20to%20be%20able%20to%20help%20our%20kids%20who%20are%20in%20school%20right%20now.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%226b5dfed6-2bb1-4b2a-aedc-b63b9c51b93a%5C%22%3EDifferent%20regulations%20from%20state%20to%20state%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ERegulations%20for%20microschools%20vary%20by%20state.%C2%A0An%20analysis%20by%20the%3Cstrong%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3ENational%20Microschooling%20Center%C2%A0found%20that%3Cstrong%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3Eover%20half%20of%20microschools%20follow%20their%20state's%20homeschooling%20requirements%2C%20while%20the%20rest%20either%20follow%20their%20state's%20nonpublic%20school%20guidelines%20or%20operate%20in%20a%20state%20with%20a%20defined%20microschool%20statute.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWest%20Virginia%2C%20for%20example%2C%20codified%20the%20legal%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.wvlegislature.gov%2FBill_Status%2Fbills_text.cfm%3Fbilldoc%3DSB268%2520SUB1%2520eng.htm%26yr%3D2022%26sesstype%3DRS%26i%3D268%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Edefinition%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20a%20microschool%20in%202022%2C%20which%20says%20that%20one%20or%20more%20teachers%20can%20create%20a%20school%20that%20charges%20tuition%20and%20is%20an%20alternative%20to%20public%2C%20private%2C%20and%20homeschool%20enrollment.%20Georgia%20codified%20the%20legal%20definition%20of%20a%20learning%20pod%20one%20year%20prior%2C%20which%20could%20include%20a%20microschool%20structure.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHaving%20those%20legal%20definitions%20allows%20regulators%20to%20ensure%20microschools%20are%20meeting%20the%20necessary%20requirements%2C%20Shoemaker%20DeMio%20said%20%E2%80%94%20and%20the%20lack%20of%20definitions%20from%20other%20states%20raises%20concerns%20on%20how%20to%20best%20hold%20those%20schools%20accountable.%20Lack%20of%20accountability%20could%20give%20rise%20to%20misuse%20of%20funds%20and%20inability%20to%20track%20whether%20kids%20are%20effectively%20learning%20the%20curriculum%2C%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20we%20have%20a%20way%20that%20we%20can%20categorize%20certain%20schools%20as%20microschools%2C%20then%20we're%20able%20to%20actually%20break%20down%20the%20data%20and%20we're%20able%20to%20better%20understand%20who%20these%20students%20are%20serving%20and%20what%20quality%20of%20education%20they're%20receiving%20or%20how%20they're%20achieving%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESome%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Emicroschools%20have%20been%20investigated%20for%20accusations%20of%20misusing%20funds.%20Arizona's%20attorney%20general%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.azcentral.com%2Fstory%2Fnews%2Flocal%2Farizona-education%2F2021%2F04%2F26%2Farizona-attorney-general-probes-prenda-edkey-microschools%2F7359925002%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Elaunched%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0an%20investigation%20in%202021%20into%20a%20microschool%20company%2C%20accusing%20it%20of%20collecting%20charter%20school%20funding%20from%20the%20state%20without%20actually%20providing%20any%20curriculum.%20In%20West%20Virginia%2C%20the%20state's%20treasurer%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwestvirginiawatch.com%2F2024%2F03%2F04%2Ffailed-west-virginia-microschool-fuels-state-probe-and-some-soul-searching%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eincluded%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0a%20microschool%20in%20an%20investigation%20following%20complaints%20from%20parents%20that%20their%20tuition%20was%20not%20being%20used%20to%20teach%20their%20children.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFairhead%20said%20that%20she%20doesn't%20think%20more%20regulations%20are%20necessary%20and%20that%20they%20could%20diminish%20teachers'%20passion.%20She%20said%20that%20parents%20hold%20her%20accountable%3A%20%26quot%3BThey%20ask%20questions.%20They%20want%20to%20know%20what%20we're%20teaching%20and%20what%20our%20kids%20are%20learning.%20And%20I%20prefer%20them%20to%20be%20my%20accountability%20over%20somebody%20who%20doesn't%20know%20my%20kids%2C%20doesn't%20know%20our%20area%2C%20and%20doesn't%20know%20me.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShoemaker%20DeMio%20said%20that%20absent%20clear%20guidelines%2C%20data%20on%20microschools%20and%20student%20outcomes%20will%20remain%20minimal.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20we%20can%20get%20specific%20regulations%20and%20guidance%20at%20the%20state%20level%2C%20that%20would%20be%20really%20helpful.%20It%20can%20provide%20us%20with%20data%20so%20that%20we%20could%20better%20track%20the%20schools%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20%26quot%3BBut%20at%20the%20same%20time%2C%20it%20would%20also%20be%20helpful%20for%20people%20interested%20in%20starting%20microschools%20if%20they%20have%20a%20better%20understanding%2C%20if%20they%20have%20better%20guidance%20from%20the%20state%20on%20how%20to%20go%20about%20this.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EDo%20you%20have%20experience%20with%20microschooling%20or%20alternative%20forms%20of%20education%3F%20Share%20your%20story%20with%20this%20reporter%20at%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22mailto%3A%2520asheffey%40businessinsider.com%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3Easheffey%40businessinsider.com%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhat-is-a-microschool-pros-cons-personalized-learning-new-education-2025-6%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1749107942000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6837171bca50259add4d2bc7%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhat-is-a-microschool-pros-cons-personalized-learning-new-education-2025-6%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22During%20the%20pandemic%2C%20a%20growing%20number%20of%20parents%20wanted%20an%20alternative%20to%20the%20traditional%20public%20school.%20That's%20where%20microschools%20come%20in.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22asheffey%40businessinsider.com%20(Ayelet%20Sheffey)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A68%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhat-is-a-microschool-pros-cons-personalized-learning-new-education-2025-6%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Trump's%20new%20tra